intro: Fimbristylis oritrephes, commonly known as the narrow-leaf flat sedge, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It is a member of the Cyperaceae family, which includes sedges and related plants. The plant typically grows in wet or seasonally wet environments, such as marshes and swampy areas. It has narrow, grass-like leaves and produces small, spike-like inflorescences. Its botanical features make it an important component of wetland ecosystems.
